'''Agim Hajrizi''' (born [[Mitrovica, Kosovo]], (former [[Yugoslavia]]), was an [[Albania]]n [[activist]] for [[human rights]] and the [[president]] of the Union of Independent Trade Unions of Kosova (BSPK). Agim Hajrizi was [[murder]]ed by [[Serbia|Serb]] [[paramilitary]] soldiers in his home in Mitrovica on 24 March 1999, with his mother Nazmie and 12-year-old son Ilir. It is thought he was targeted for his political activities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greekhelsinki.gr/english/pressrelease/hlc-18-11-2000.html|title=HLC - Press Release - 18/11/2000   The Balkan Human Rights Web Pages|work=greekhelsinki.gr}}</ref>

[[File:Pllaka Përkujtimore te Shtëpia e Agim Hajrizit, Mitrovicë.jpg|thumb|Commemorative plaques at the House of Agim Hajrizi, in Mitrovicë]]

