'''Reassurance policing''' is a model of policing that centers on [[signal crime]]s. Developed in the [[United Kingdom]], reassurance policing aims to identify "signals", and involve the community in solving community-related problems (similar to the community policing model).<ref>{{cite book|title=Introduction to Policing|year=2011|publisher=SAGE Publications, Inc|isbn=978-1412975308|editor-last=Scaramella|editor-first=Gene L.|editor2-last=Cox|editor2-first=Steven|editor3-last=McCamey|editor3-first=William P.}}</ref>
